						               													<description>The Refugee Searching for Hope, is a solo/cooperative game where players must work together to gather resources, build structures to create a safe path and guide the refugee to a safe place, meanwhile avoiding the &amp;quot;Shadow of War&amp;quot; that destroys and consumes everything in their way. The Refugee must reach the safe spot at any cost, even at the player's life.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you have 4 Action Points that can be spend in multiple and/pr a single action, these actions are:&amp;#10;-Advance on the pathway to discover the land, represented by cards of Resources/Hazards over tiles that create the pathway. But beware you cannot come back.&amp;#10;-Recover Resources, taking 1 Card from the pathway tiles. Be careful not to take too many resources or you will attract the attention of the militia. Look out for the &amp;ldquo;Hope Cards&amp;rdquo; this are the most valuable resources but also the most fragile and scarce.&amp;#10;-Guiding People, by moving a group or individual from a tile to an adjacent one by using the Resource necessary to overcome the Hazard. This is the only way to move the Refugee.&amp;#10;-Build a Structure, Structure provides benefits to the players and protection to the Refugee; you must build them to win special actions. This will help you and your fellow travellers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The danger lurks! After you finish your turn, the pathway is filled with new card representing potential Resources and Hazards, but, if you reveal a &amp;ldquo;Shadow of War&amp;rdquo; Card the Shadow of War is going to move towards you, eliminating any &amp;ldquo;Hope&amp;rdquo; revealed and destroy everything in their way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players will win the game if they built a Campsite in the last tile of the pathway and guide successfully the Refugee to it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But players will lose the game if any and/or multiple conditions are met:&amp;#10;-The Trial Deck runs out and there aren&amp;rsquo;t enough cards to refill the pathway, players run out of time and resources!&amp;#10;-The &amp;ldquo;Shadow of War&amp;rdquo; consumes the Refugee, you fail had fail your mission.&amp;#10;-All the players have been gravely injured and took out of the pathway, it was too much risk to continue, and you abandoned the refugee.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
